"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731136","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>The UK has engaged counterparts in the African Union– particularly the Southern African Development Community – on the 2018 Presidential elections in Zimbabwe. We have highlighted that a democratic, prosperous and stable Zimbabwe is in the interests of the whole region and urged them to do what they can to encourage free and fair elections.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-06-29T12:39:36.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731136/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731136/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731136/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-21","Zimbabwe: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions his Department has had with counterparts in the African Union on free and fair elections in the Republic of Zimbabwe in 2018.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","101"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731137","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-06-30","<p>The BEIS Ministerial Team has undertaken several visits across Scotland this year, as part of the Department’s stakeholder engagement for an Industrial Strategy that works for the whole of the UK and drives growth right across the country.</p><p>Most recently, my right hon. Friend the Secretary of State visited Scotland for two days during which he hosted a reception at Edinburgh University on 11 April which was attended by over 100 businesses from all over Scotland. This was followed by visits in the region.</p><p>The Ministerial team has and continues to visit numerous businesses around the UK to prioritise engagement on Industrial Strategy.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-06-30T12:09:45.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731137/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731137/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731137/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-06-21","Domestic Visits: Glasgow East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, on which date (a) he or (b) a Minister of his Department last visited a company headquartered in Glasgow East constituency.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731138","Department for Transport","false","2017-06-27","<p>Ministers regularly visit a variety of places across the country. We do not however have a record of a Department for Transport Minister specifically visiting Baillieston test centre in Glasgow.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-06-27T13:47:26.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731138/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731138/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731138/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-21","Driving Tests: Glasgow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, on which date a Minister of his Department last visited Baillieston DVSA test centre in Glasgow.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731139","Department for Transport","false","2017-06-27","<p>As at 31 May 2017, the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) has (a) 5 part time employees and (b) 7 full time employees based at Baillieston test centre in Glasgow.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-06-27T13:50:23.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731139/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731139/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731139/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-21","Driving Tests: Glasgow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many (a) part-time and (b) full-time employees are based at Baillieston DVSA test centre in Glasgow.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","104"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731140","Department for Transport","false","2017-06-27","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency leases Glasgow Baillieston driving test centre from the pension fund of a non-departmental public body – the Medical Research Pension Trust Ltd. The building is managed by Lambert Smith Hampton.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-06-27T13:54:01.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731140/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731140/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731140/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-21","Driving Tests: Glasgow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, which landlord provides accommodation for Baillieston DVSA test centre in Glasgow.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","105"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731141","Home Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>Our records indicate that the number of asylum cases awaiting an asylum decision at 31 March 2017 where the latest address is in the Glasgow East constituency is 109.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-06-29T14:54:31.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731141/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731141/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731141/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-21","Asylum: Glasgow East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many asylum seekers are resident in Glasgow East constituency.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","106"
