he CPS only retains data on those orders in which it assists in the enforcement process. The latest data relates to March 2017.</p><p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2017-06-26T15:54:38.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731179/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731179/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731179/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-06-21","Confiscation Orders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, with reference to the Answer of 20 April 2017 to Question 70644, on confiscation orders, what the outstanding debt is by Crown Prosecution Service Area.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731180","Department for Transport","false","2017-06-28","<p>As with all transport scheme proposals a thorough analysis is being carried out by my department to ensure it is a robust scheme. This includes examining whether the National Infrastructure Commission’s detailed recommendations on the scheme have been taken into account. The next steps and timescales, including when the next stage of public consultation will take place, will therefore be decided as part of this analysis.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard","204 ; 206","2017-06-28T13:41:26.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731180/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731180/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731180/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-21","Crossrail 2 Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when the next stage of public consultation for Crossrail 2 is planned to take place.","false","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","205"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731181","Department for Transport","false","2017-06-28","<p>As with all transport scheme proposals a thorough analysis is being carried out by my department to ensure it is a robust scheme. This includes examining whether the National Infrastructure Commission’s detailed recommendations on the scheme have been taken into account. The next steps and timescales, including when the next stage of public consultation will take place, will therefore be decided as part of this analysis.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard","204 ; 205","2017-06-28T13:41:26.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731181/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731181/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731181/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-21","Crossrail 2 Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the Government's plans are for implementing Crossrail 2.","false","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731182","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-06-28","<p>The potential merits of matching basic benefit levels to the JRF’s Minimum Income Standard have not been assessed.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-06-28T16:33:26.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731182/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731182/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731182/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-06-21","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will make an assessment of the potential merits of matching basic benefit levels to the Minimum Income Standards calculated annually by the Joseph Rowntree Foundation.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731183","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-06-26","<p>The British Olympic Association is responsible for the trading name and branding of the Olympic team representing Great Britain and Northern Ireland, the Isle of Man, the Channel Islands and the UK Overseas Territories.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-06-26T16:54:41.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731183/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731183/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731183/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-06-21","Olympic Games","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what plans she has to ensure that the UK Olympic team is referred to as Team UK rather than Team GB.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731184","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-06-26","<p>The government is currently considering over 140,000 responses to the consultation on the Leveson Inquiry and its implementation.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-06-26T16:13:31.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731184/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731184/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731184/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-06-21","Culture, Practices and Ethics of the Press Inquiry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when she plans to publish her response to her Department's consultation on the Leveson Inquiry and its implementation; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","230"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731185","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-06-29","<p>No central assessment has been carried out. The costs will vary widely based on the size and age of buildings. Local authorities may have commissioned separate assessments into the costs involved following the Government’s request in 2013 to social housing providers that they consider installing sprinklers into older residential tower blocks.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-06-29T17:30:26.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731185/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731185/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731185/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-06-21","High Rise Flats: Fire Extinguishers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate the Government has made of the average cost per flat of retrofitting sprinkler systems for fire safety in tower blocks.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731186","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-06-26","<p>The government is currently considering over 140,000 responses to the consultation on this issue.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-06-26T16:15:54.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731186/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731186/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731186/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-06-21","Mass Media: Legal Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what plans she has to repeal section 40 of the Crime and Courts Act 2013.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731187","Home Office","false","2017-06-26","<p>A temporary hold on decision-making in respect of some partner visa applications was introduced on 22 February so that the implications of the Supreme Court judgment handed down that day in MM (Lebanon) &amp; Others could be considered.</p><p>The partner visa applications affected are those under Appendix FM to the Immigration Rules which fall to be refused and which involve a child or do not meet the minimum income requirement. The temporary hold will be lifted once the judgment's findings have been addressed.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","299 ; 300","2017-06-26T16:46:13.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731187/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731187/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731187/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-21","Visas: Married People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many applications for partner visas for which the additional fee for fast track service has been paid are affected by the suspension on processing applications as a result of the legal challenge to the Government's minimum-income requirement.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","526"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731188","Home Office","false","2017-06-26","<p>We will make sure that all victims of the Grenfell Tower tragedy, irrespective of their immigration status, will be able to access the services they need, including accommodation and healthcare. We will not use this tragic incident as a reason to carry out immigration checks on those providing vital information to identify victims.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-06-26T10:50:58.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731188/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731188/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731188/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-21","Grenfell Tower: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will ensure that information provided by survivors of Grenfell Tower about residency or immigration status will not be used for criminal investigation or affect rehousing rights.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731189","Department for Transport","false","2017-06-29","<p>In addition to providing support to those with a disability, the original intention of the English national concessionary bus pass scheme was to help people maintain their independence in retirement. Concessions are therefore not aimed at people considered to be of working age and in April 2010 the concession was specifically aligned for both men and women to the Department for Work and Pensions’ State Pension Age.</p><p> </p><p>Local authorities have the discretion to offer concessions over and above the statutory minimum to their residents as they see fit.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-06-29T14:23:14.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731189/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731189/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731189/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-21","Travel: Concessions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has made an estimate of the potential cost to extend entitlement to free travel passes to women born in the 1950s who have yet to reach state pension age.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731190","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-06-26","<p>The Department has been working on a wide ranging review of Building Regulations, including fire safety issues and including simplifying the guidance, as recommended by the Coroner. We are considering the best way to take forward this work in the light of the Grenfell Tower fire.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-06-26T16:29:12.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731190/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731190/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731190/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-06-21","High Rise Flats: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when the review of fire regulations and safety in tower blocks following the fire at Lakanal House in Lambeth began; who has been consulted in that review; and whether the review was delayed or postponed after it began.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","451"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731191","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-06-28","<p>The Government is committed to ensuring content creators are appropriately rewarded for the content they make available online while also ensuring that we continue to encourage investment in new content and innovative services. The Government is currently engaging with these issues as part of the EU Digital Single Market initiative, where we are negotiating a package of measures which seek to support fairness in the online value chain. The Government will continue to ensure there is a robust system for protection of intellectual property when the UK has left the EU, with strong protections against infringement.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-06-28T12:54:18.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731191/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731191/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731191/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-06-21","Arts: Electronic Commerce","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will ensure content creators are paid for the content they make available online.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731192","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-06-30","<p>The commercial radio deregulation consultation closed on 8 May 2017. We intend to publish the government response in due course.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-06-30T11:38:25.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731192/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731192/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731192/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-06-21","Commercial Broadcasting: Radio","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when she plans to publish her response to the consultation on Commercial Radio Deregulation which closed in May 2017; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731193","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-06-28","<p>We believe investment in arts and culture increases the economic, social and wellbeing benefits for individuals and communities. DCMS will continue to work with our sectors to explore new and innovative ways in which cultural investment can be used to foster economic growth in local areas whilst also benefitting the wider communities.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2017-06-28T14:30:16.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731193/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731193/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731193/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-06-21","Culture: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when she plans to introduce the new cultural development fund to use cultural investment to turn around communities; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731194","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Government remains committed to developing a constructive relationship with Iran, building on the reopening of our Embassy in Tehran and the upgrade of our diplomatic relationship. We are exploring discussions with Iran on a range of issues, including human rights, where we regularly raise concerns with the Government of Iran on the use of the death penalty and the lack of freedom of political or religious belief. In the future we hope to be in a position to discuss other issues, including support for people with disabilities in the country.</p><p>The Foreign Secretary regularly speaks to the International Development Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Witham (Priti Patel) on a range of issues. The appointment of Joint Ministers of State for the Foreign and Commonwealth Office and the Department of International Development further aligns these two departments, helping to facilitate discussions on a host of important subjects.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-06-29T12:47:20.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731194/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731194/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731194/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-21","Iran: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with (a) the Secretary of State for International Development and (b) the Government of Iran on support for people with disabilities in that country.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","503"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731195","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>While we have not had any specific discussions with the Israeli or Lebanese authorities on this issue, we encourage all attempts to resolve the dispute.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-06-29T12:54:13.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731195/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731195/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731195/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-21","Israel and Lebanon: Minerals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions his Department has had with the (a) Government of Israel and (b) Government of Lebanon on disputed mineral-rich areas of the eastern Mediterranean.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731196","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-06-29","<p>HM Government is committed to involving the Overseas Territories, including the Falkland Islands, as we prepare to exit the EU, and ensuring their interests are properly taken into account. Ministers and leaders of the Overseas Territories have committed to taking forward future engagement through the creation of the UK – Overseas Territories Joint Ministerial Council on European Negotiations (JMC – OT EN), which I chaired, which met for the first time in February and will meet again on the 12th July.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-06-29T10:30:01.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731196/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731196/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731196/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-06-21","Brexit: Falkland Islands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what discussions he has had with representatives of the Falkland Islands Government on that Government's role in discussions on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","505"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731197","Home Office","false","2017-06-26","<p>The Government has significantly improved its understanding of the threat from all forms of extremism through the work of the Extremism Analysis Unit. The Counter Extremism Strategy sets out the action the Government is taking to tackle extremism wherever it occurs.</p><p>Through the Prevent strand of the CONTEST counter-terrorism strategy we are safeguarding individuals who are vulnerable to radicalisation, and are currently working with over 80 civil society groups and statutory partners to build resilience in communities against radicalisation.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-06-26T13:31:28.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731197/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731197/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731197/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-21","Radicalism: Birmingham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking to (a) monitor and (b) control increases in levels of (i) extremism and (ii) radicalised Islam in Birmingham.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","506"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731198","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-06-30","<p>The British Government holds regular discussions with the Government of Japan and the Republic of Korea (ROK) on the widest range of security issues, including the recent missile launches conducted by the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK). In May, the Prime Minister, spoke to the President of the ROK to confirm that the UK will continue to work with the ROK and the international community to maintain pressure on the DPRK to abide by its international obligations, including multiple UN Security Council Resolutions which prohibit its ballistic missile programme. In April, the Prime Minister and Japanese Prime Minister Abe held talks at Chequers and agreed on the severity of the threat posed by the DPRK and the need for international coordination.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-06-30T12:43:09.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731198/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731198/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731198/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-21","North Korea: Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions the Government has had with the Governments of (a) Japan and (b) South Korea on recent missile launches conducted by North Korea.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","507"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731199","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Government remains absolutely committed to LGBT equality and the Prime Minister has been very clear that any arrangement with the DUP will not affect LGBT rights in the UK. This is a devolved matter and is therefore for a reformed Northern Ireland Executive to determine.</p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2017-06-29T15:06:57.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731199/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731199/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731199/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-21","Marriage: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether he has made representations to the Democratic Unionist Party leader, Arlene Foster on the extension of (a) civil partnerships and (b) same-sex marriage in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","508"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731200","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-06-30","<p>DCMS does not hold data on entrance fees for charged temporary exhibitions at national museums in England over the last five years. DCMS-sponsored national museums operate at arm's length from government and decisions about entrance fees for temporary exhibitions are taken independently by these organisations.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2017-06-30T13:31:17.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731200/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731200/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731200/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-06-21","Museums and Galleries: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate she has made of the trends in the entrance fees charged for temporary exhibitions at national museums in England in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","409"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731201","Department of Health","false","2017-06-27","<p>Since the announcement in 2015 of the intention to allow local authorities (LAs) to retain 100% of their income from business rates, officials at the Department of Health have held regular discussions on the implications for LA public health funding and services with their counterparts in the Department for Communities and Local Government and with representative bodies. We expect these discussions to continue and have already confirmed that the ring-fenced public health grant for LAs will stay in place for the remainder of 2017/18 and for 2018/19. Any proposed changes to the regulations prescribing particular services or steps will be subject to public consultation.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","266 ; 267 ; 268","2017-06-27T10:34:35.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731201/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731201/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731201/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-21","Public Health: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether his Department plans to extend the period of the ring fence on the public health grant until plans to fund local authorities through 100 per cent business rates retention are implemented after 2020.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","551"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731202","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-06-26","<p>In line with civil service guidance, work to establish the Working Group was paused during the recent pre-election period. Defra officials will be establishing the Working Group soon, with the aim of the Group providing advice to Ministers in the new year.</p><p> </p><p>Once the Working Group has been established, I will write to the hon. Member with details of its membership and place a copy in the library of the House</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","293 ; 294","2017-06-26T14:00:18.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731202/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731202/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731202/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-06-21","Beverage Containers: Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, with reference to page 34 of the Government's Litter Strategy for England published in April 2017, whether the timeline for his Department's Working Group on Voluntary and Economic Incentives Reduce Litter to consider the advantages and disadvantages of different types of deposit and reward and return schemes for drinks containers, and to produce advice by the end of 2017, still stands.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731203","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-06-26","<p>In line with civil service guidance, work to establish the Working Group was paused during the recent pre-election period. Defra officials will be establishing the Working Group soon, with the aim of the Group providing advice to Ministers in the new year.</p><p> </p><p>Once the Working Group has been established, I will write to the hon. Member with details of its membership and place a copy in the library of the House</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","292 ; 294","2017-06-26T14:00:18.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731203/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731203/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731203/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-06-21","Beverage Containers: Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, with reference to page 34 of the Government's Litter Strategy for England published in April 2017, if he will provide regular updates to Parliament on the progress of discussions of his Department's Working Group on Voluntary and Economic Incentives to Reduce Litter considering the advantages and disadvantages of different types of deposit and reward and return schemes for drinks containers.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731204","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-06-26","<p>In line with civil service guidance, work to establish the Working Group was paused during the recent pre-election period. Defra officials will be establishing the Working Group soon, with the aim of the Group providing advice to Ministers in the new year.</p><p> </p><p>Once the Working Group has been established, I will write to the hon. Member with details of its membership and place a copy in the library of the House</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","292 ; 293","2017-06-26T14:00:18.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731204/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731204/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731204/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-06-21","Voluntary and Economic Incentives to Reduce Litter Working Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, with reference to page 79 of the Government's Litter Strategy for England published in April 2017, if he will publish the membership  of his Department's Working Group on Voluntary and Economic Incentives Reduce Litter.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731205","Department of Health","false","2017-06-27","<p>Since the announcement in 2015 of the intention to allow local authorities (LAs) to retain 100% of their income from business rates, officials at the Department of Health have held regular discussions on the implications for LA public health funding and services with their counterparts in the Department for Communities and Local Government and with representative bodies. We expect these discussions to continue and have already confirmed that the ring-fenced public health grant for LAs will stay in place for the remainder of 2017/18 and for 2018/19. Any proposed changes to the regulations prescribing particular services or steps will be subject to public consultation.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","267 ; 268 ; 551","2017-06-27T10:34:35.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731205/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731205/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731205/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-21","Public Health: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions his Department has had with the Department of Communities and Local Government on the future administration of the public health grant.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731206","Department of Health","false","2017-06-27","<p>On 4 October 2016 my Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Health announced that the number of medical training places available to students in England each year will be expanded by 1,500 to ensure the National Health Service in England has the future supply of doctors it needs to continue to provide safe, compassionate care.</p><p> </p><p>In September 2018, the Government will fund 500 additional student places through medical schools in England each year. A public consultation on how best to allocate a further 1,000 additional places closed on 2 June 2017. The Higher Education Funding Council for England will publish details on the allocation process over the coming months. These 1,000 places will be available to students from September 2019.</p><p> </p><p>Health Education England is responsible for ensuring that there is sufficient future supply of staff to meet the workforce requirements of the English health system. Information on future supply and specialty fill rates can be found in Health Education England’s Workforce Plan for England, available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.hee.nhs.uk/sites/default/files/documents/HEE%20commissioning%20and%20investment%20plan%202016-17_0.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.hee.nhs.uk/sites/default/files/documents/HEE%20commissioning%20and%20investment%20plan%202016-17_0.pdf</a></p><p>Availability of medical school places at universities in the devolved administrations is a matter for the individual Government in each administration.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-06-27T15:15:03.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731206/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731206/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731206/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-21","Medicine: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to increase capacity at medical schools to meet demand from applicants with high level qualifications.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731207","Department of Health","false","2017-06-27","<p>The number of individual diagnoses of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) is not held. The statistics provided are the number of finished admission episodes.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease</p></td><td><p>Chronic Lower Respiratory Disease (relating to COPD)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>109,570</p></td><td><p>125,934</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>117,897</p></td><td><p>135,859</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>113,876</p></td><td><p>132,163</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>123,518</p></td><td><p>143,233</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>124,298</p></td><td><p>144,327</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-06-27T10:41:14.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731207/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731207/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731207/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-21","Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people have been diagnosed with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","316"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731208","Department of Health","false","2017-06-27","<p>There is a range of treatment options for brain cancer, including radiotherapy, chemotherapy and neurosurgery. Where neurosurgery is indicated, an appropriate procedure will be selected for each patient which does include minimally invasive procedures and as such there are no plans to roll out keyhole surgery.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-06-27T10:38:01.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731208/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731208/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731208/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-21","Brain Cancer: Surgery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the timetable is for the roll-out of keyhole surgery for brain cancer patients on the NHS.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731209","Department of Health","false","2017-06-27","<p>Lyme disease is a bacterial infection transmitted between animals and humans by infected ticks. Dogs can pick up infected ticks outdoors and bring them into the home or garden, which could lead to Lyme disease in any bitten human. There is no evidence to show that Lyme disease can be transmitted from person-to-person, therefore dog walkers cannot contribute to the spread of the disease.</p><p> </p><p>Public Health England (PHE) provides advice to the public on being tick aware, how to remove ticks and the signs and symptoms of Lyme disease. This information is available through the GOV.UK website and is relevant to dog walkers as well as the general public and can be used by local authorities in their own advice. PHE has also helped revise the patient advice on NHS Choices and the Government website contains links to Lyme disease information.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/552740/Ticksandyourhealthinfoabouttickbites.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/552740/Ticksandyourhealthinfoabouttickbites.pdf</a></p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/463701/LymeDisease_SignsAndSymptoms.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/463701/LymeDisease_SignsAndSymptoms.pdf</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-06-27T10:38:13.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731209/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731209/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731209/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-21","Lyme Disease: Disease Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to monitor and control the spread of Lyme disease by dog walkers.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731210","Department for Transport","false","2017-06-29","<p>Permission is required from the Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) to fly a kite above 60m, in accordance with Article 92 of the Air Navigation Order 2016.</p><p> </p><p>The CAA has a dedicated page on its website containing guidance on the rules and regulations relating to kite flying in the UK. The CAA intends to shortly commence an email campaign directed at UK kite associations, organisations and clubs with information on the existing regulations relating to kite flying and the CAA permissions process.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-06-29T12:35:25.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731210/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731210/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731210/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-21","Kites","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to monitor and control kite-fighting contests.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","319"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731211","HM Treasury","false","2017-06-30","<p>The 2015 National Risk Assessment of Money Laundering and Terrorist Financing found that the effectiveness of the supervisory regime in the UK is inconsistent and, whilst some supervisors are highly effective in some areas, there is room for improvement across the board. The National Risk Assessment is available at: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/uk-national-risk-assessment-of-money-laundering-and-terrorist-financing</p><p> </p><p>The government committed to review the regime and, in March, announced reforms to address the issues identified in the National Risk Assessment. More information on these reforms is available at: https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/anti-money-laundering-supervisory-regime-response-and-call-for-further-information</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-06-30T11:29:28.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731211/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731211/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731211/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-06-21","Money Laundering: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of having 27 separate supervisory bodies responsible for guarding against money laundering.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","321"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731212","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-06-30","<p>The Secretary of State has had a number of discussions on EU exit with Arlene Foster and other Northern Ireland Ministers under the previous Northern Ireland Executive, including through the Joint Ministerial Committee. There is a very strong commitment from the UK Government, Irish Government and Northern Ireland parties to find a practical solution that recognises the unique circumstances of the land border between Northern Ireland and Ireland. We welcome the clear commitment from the European Council and European Commission to work on flexible and imaginative solutions to aim to avoid a return to a hard border.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-06-30T14:05:06.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731212/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731212/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731212/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-06-21","Borders: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what discussions he has had with the Democratic Unionist Party leader, Arlene Foster, on the land border between Northern Ireland and the Republic of Ireland.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","322"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731213","Women and Equalities","false","2017-08-31","<p>My Rt hon. Friend, the Secretary of State, has a continued dialogue with my Rt hon. Friend, the Prime Minister, on a range of issues that affect government. My Rt hon. Friend, the Secretary of State, in her recent debate on equalities and women’s rights in the House, made clear the UK’s proud record of promoting equality. We have some of the strongest laws in the world to prevent and tackle discrimination and my Rt hon. Friend, the Prime Minister, has provided reassurance that we will continue to strengthen our progressive record on equality and human rights as we work with others to govern in the national interest.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-08-31T15:48:34.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731213/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731213/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731213/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-06-21","Females: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, whether she had made representations to the Prime Minister on women's rights in Northern Ireland prior to the Prime Minister meeting with Democratic Unionist Party leader, Arlene Foster, on 13 June.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","323"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731214","Women and Equalities","false","2017-07-12","<p>The United Kingdom is recognised as a global leader on LGBT rights and I am immensely proud of our record. We have one of the strongest legislative frameworks to prevent and tackle all forms of discrimination, including on the grounds of sexual orientation and gender reassignment. The Government is committed to LGBT equality. As we work with others to govern in the national interest, we will continue to promote and champion the equal rights we believe in.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-07-12T16:34:27.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731214/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731214/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731214/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-06-21","LGBT People: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, whether she had made representations to the Prime Minister on LGBT rights in Northern Ireland prior to the Prime Minister meeting with Democratic Unionist Party leader, Arlene Foster, on 13 June.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","324"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731215","Department of Health","false","2017-06-27","<p>Since the announcement in 2015 of the intention to allow local authorities (LAs) to retain 100% of their income from business rates, officials at the Department of Health have held regular discussions on the implications for LA public health funding and services with their counterparts in the Department for Communities and Local Government and with representative bodies. We expect these discussions to continue and have already confirmed that the ring-fenced public health grant for LAs will stay in place for the remainder of 2017/18 and for 2018/19. Any proposed changes to the regulations prescribing particular services or steps will be subject to public consultation.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","266 ; 268 ; 551","2017-06-27T10:34:35.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731215/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731215/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731215/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-21","Public Health: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans he has to hold discussions with representative organisations in public health on the mandated public health duties of local authorities in light of the Government's plan to devolve the public health grant.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731216","Department of Health","false","2017-06-27","<p>Since the announcement in 2015 of the intention to allow local authorities (LAs) to retain 100% of their income from business rates, officials at the Department of Health have held regular discussions on the implications for LA public health funding and services with their counterparts in the Department for Communities and Local Government and with representative bodies. We expect these discussions to continue and have already confirmed that the ring-fenced public health grant for LAs will stay in place for the remainder of 2017/18 and for 2018/19. Any proposed changes to the regulations prescribing particular services or steps will be subject to public consultation.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","266 ; 267 ; 551","2017-06-27T10:34:35.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731216/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731216/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731216/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-21","Public Health: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans he has to hold discussions with representative organisations in sexual health, drugs and alcohol services on the mandated public health duties of local authorities in light of the Government's plan to devolve the public health grant.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731217","Home Office","false","2017-06-26","<p>A temporary hold on decision-making in respect of some partner visa applications was introduced on 22 February so that the implications of the Supreme Court judgment handed down that day in MM (Lebanon) &amp; Others could be considered.</p><p>The partner visa applications affected are those under Appendix FM to the Immigration Rules which fall to be refused and which involve a child or do not meet the minimum income requirement. The temporary hold will be lifted once the judgment's findings have been addressed.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","300 ; 526","2017-06-26T16:46:13.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731217/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731217/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731217/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-21","Visas: Married People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when the Government plans to lift the suspension on the processing of certain applications for partner visas that was introduced as a result of the legal challenge to the minimum income requirement.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731218","Department of Health","false","2017-06-26","<p>The Government is developing a new tobacco control plan, which will be published shortly.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","43","2017-06-26T14:01:39.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731218/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731218/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731218/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-21","Tobacco","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when his Department plans to publish the updated Tobacco Control Plan; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731219","Home Office","false","2017-06-26","<p>A temporary hold on decision-making in respect of some partner visa applications was introduced on 22 February so that the implications of the Supreme Court judgment handed down that day in MM (Lebanon) &amp; Others could be considered.</p><p>The partner visa applications affected are those under Appendix FM to the Immigration Rules which fall to be refused and which involve a child or do not meet the minimum income requirement. The temporary hold will be lifted once the judgment's findings have been addressed.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","299 ; 526","2017-06-26T16:46:13.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731219/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731219/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731219/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-21","Visas: Married People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many partner visa applications are affected by the suspension of processing applications as a result of the legal challenge to the Government's minimum income requirement.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731220","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-06-28","<p>​We enjoy a strong bilateral relationship with Hungary. Officials at the British Embassy in Budapest routinely discuss economic and political developments with the Hungarian Government. Migration is also regularly discussed in EU fora.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-06-28T16:03:33.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731220/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731220/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731220/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-21","Hungary: Economic Growth and Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions his Department has had with the Hungarian Government on (a) refugee movements and (b) economic development in that country.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731221","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-06-27","<p>​As far as we are aware there have been no such discussions in recent times. The British Government is clear, however, that discrimination on the basis of faith is a violation of universal human rights. The right not to be discriminated against by the state extends to the provision of marriage.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-06-27T13:53:56.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731221/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731221/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731221/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-21","Middle East: Religious Freedom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions his Department has had with governments in the Middle East to encourage a better understanding of human rights provision relating to inter-faith marriages.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731222","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-06-28","<p>My right hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Defence visited the Falklands Islands in February 2016, and met with members of the Falkland Islands Government to discuss a range of issues. The joint Ministry of Defence and Foreign and Commonwealth Office funded Falkland Islands demining programme is making significant progress towards meeting the UK's obligations under the Anti-Personnel Mine Ban Convention.</p><p> </p><p>The current demining phase began in October 2016, tackling the most remote, environmentally-sensitive and complex minefields on the Islands, has already recovered over 3,000 anti-personnel mines and over 150 anti-tank mines, releasing over 3.5 million square metres back to the Islanders. The UK continues to keep the Anti-Personnel Mine Ban Convention informed of its progress.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-06-28T15:24:18.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731222/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731222/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731222/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-06-21","Falkland Islands: Land mines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with the Government of the Falkland Islands on support for mine-clearing operations; and what the timetable is for all mine-fields in the Falkland Islands to be cleared.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731223","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-03","<p>Defra is not directly involved in developing the fishery sector in the Falkland Islands, as responsibility for fisheries management has been devolved to the Falkland Islands Government. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) is the lead department for matters relating to the Falkland Islands and Defra works closely with the FCO on wider matters relating to fisheries that are relevant to the UK Government.</p><p> </p><p>The Joint Nature Conservation Committee (JNCC) has an officer based on the Falkland Islands, part funded by Defra, who works closely with the Falklands fishing industry to help deliver commitments to reduce fisheries bycatch under the Agreement on the Conservation of Albatrosses and Petrels (ACAP).</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-07-03T09:18:06.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731223/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731223/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731223/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-06-21","Fisheries: Falkland Islands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to develop the fishery sector in the Falkland Islands in line with similar developments in the UK fishing sector.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731224","Home Office","false","2017-06-28","<p>Unexplained Wealth Orders (UWO) were placed in statute by the Criminal Finances Act which was passed on 27 April 2017. It is a powerful tool that will help tackle serious crime and international corruption. Agencies with civil recovery powers, such as the NCA and the Serious Fraud Office, can apply to the High Court for a UWO where the agency thinks that an individual holds property, and there are reasonable grounds to suspect that the known sources of the individual’s lawfully obtained income would be insufficient to enable the individual to obtain that property.</p><p>If the person provides information in response to a UWO, the enforcement authority can then decide whether to investigate further, take recovery action or take no further action. If the person does not comply with a UWO, the property identified in the order is presumed to be recoverable under any subsequent civil recovery proceedings.</p><p>However, there are a number of dependencies which must be implemented before this measure can be commenced. Work has begun on drafting new court rules and providing law enforcement agencies with guidance and training on how to use this measure. A statutory code of practice is also being drafted, and will undergo a public consultation prior to it being laid under the affirmative procedure. To ensure that law enforcement are able to confidently and robustly use UWOs, we will seek to commence UWOs once all these dependencies are in place.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben  Wallace",,"2017-06-28T13:04:46.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731224/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731224/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731224/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-21","Unexplained Wealth Orders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when the Government plans for Unexplained Wealth Orders to come into operation.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731225","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-25","<p>In December 2016, Defra consulted on proposals to introduce Nitrogen Dioxide (NO2) emissions controls on generators alongside its consultation on proposals for the implementation of the Medium Combustion Plant Directive (MCPD), aimed at improving air quality. The definition of generators used in the proposal captures those with a rated input of between 1MW thermal and 50MW thermal, although site aggregation means that some plants below this amount may also be affected if the total input on the same site falls within the proposed range. Insufficient controls on diesel generator emissions risk distorting electricity markets by encouraging new diesel at the expense of cleaner gas generation. Following the consultation on tightening controls, the 2016/17 capacity market auctions resulted in significantly fewer new diesel projects. While the proposed regulations relate to air quality, actions which reduce the use of diesel generators would limit carbon emissions.</p><p>The Defra consultation closed on 18 February and a response will be issued in due course.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-25T15:59:15.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731225/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731225/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731225/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-06-21","Diesel Engines: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent assessment he has made of the effectiveness of regulations for small diesel power plants.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","200"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731226","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-27","<p>The Global Forum for Asset Recovery (GFAR) was announced in May 2016. The US and UK will co-host the inaugural meeting by end 2017. This will be an opportunity to progress asset recovery cases, focusing on Nigeria, Sri Lanka, Tunisia and the Ukraine.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-06-27T14:51:39.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731226/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731226/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731226/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-21","Global Asset Recovery Forum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether a timetable has been agreed for achieving the objectives of the Global Forum for Asset Recovery.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","199"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731227","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-06-28","<p>Many of the UK’s relationships with non-EU partners and international organisations rest in some way on our membership of the EU.</p><p>The UK will seek to maintain the relationships and cooperation it currently enjoys with non-EU partners and international organisations as it exits the EU.</p><p>We are currently conducting a detailed assessment of the agreements which will require replacement as a result of the UK’s exit from the UK and taking forward work with partners to do so.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-06-28T12:29:58.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731227/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731227/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731227/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-06-21","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what estimate he has made of the number of treaties requiring renegotiation as a result of the UK's exit from the EU.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731228","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-06-30","<p>The human rights implications of Government Bills are set out in the Explanatory Notes and summarised in the statement made under section 19 of the Human Rights Act 1998 by the Minister in charge of the Bill. Human rights issues are further considered through scrutiny by the Joint Committee on Human Rights, in correspondence with the Government where required.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-06-30T13:20:30.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731228/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731228/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731228/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-06-21","Human Rights: Impact Assessments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will make an assessment of the potential merits of carrying out human rights impact assessments for each stage of the passage of a Bill.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731229","Attorney General","false","2017-06-27","<p>The Government is committed to strengthening the UK's response to bribery, corruption, money laundering, fraud and other forms of economic crime.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is continuing to review options to improve the effectiveness of the UK's response to economic crime, and any measures resulting from this work will be announced in due course.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2017-06-27T11:08:22.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731229/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731229/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731229/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-06-21","Serious Fraud Office","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, with reference to the Serious Fraud Office's news release of 20 June 2017, SFO charges in Barclays Qatar capital raising case, whether he has re-assessed the merits of maintaining the Serious Fraud Office as a separate office.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731230","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>Combating sectarian violence in Egypt is a shared objective for the Egyptian and British Governments.</p><p>Following the recent terrorist attacks in Egypt targeting the Coptic Community, the Prime Minister, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Maidenhead (Mrs May) wrote to the President of Egypt to express her condolences and reiterate the UK's support for Egypt in its fight against terrorism. The Government continues to work closely with the Egyptian authorities on security and counter-terrorism, including through training Egyptian officers in countering improvised explosive devices and close protection.</p><p>The British Government has been clear that freedom of religious belief needs to be protected and that the ability to worship in peace is a vital component of a democratic society. We are concerned about recent reports of sectarian violence in Egypt, and welcome President Sisi's consistent calls for peaceful coexistence and the Government of Egypt's expression of support for the rights of Christians and for religious tolerance.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-06-29T12:58:22.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731230/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731230/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731230/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-21","Egypt: Christianity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what diplomatic and other support the Government has given to the Egyptian Government as a result of recent attacks on Christian churches in the country.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","372"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731231","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-06-26","<p>In April 2017 we published the Improving Lives: Helping Workless Families paper which outlined the actions we plan to take in supporting the most vulnerable families.</p><p>This included the launch of an innovative new programme to address parental conflict as this is a critical influence on the quality of parenting. Children exposed to frequent, intense and poorly resolved conflict between parents are at greater risk of poor social, emotional and cognitive outcomes. The new programme will support the use of evidence-based interventions to reduce parental conflict, delivered by specialist organisations at a local level. This will transform lives by supporting parents, whether they are together or separated.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-06-26T14:14:50.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731231/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731231/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731231/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-06-21","Parents: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the then Prime Minister's speech on Life Chances on 11 January 2016, when the Government expects to implement the significant expansion in parenting programmes.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","201"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731232","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>Since 2011 the UK has committed over £436m to Lebanon, including over £340m in humanitarian and development assistance to support the country in hosting over one million Syrian refugees. This includes helping refugee children to access quality education and the provision of skills training. We also continue to provide diplomatic and technical support to the Lebanese government.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-06-29T12:41:20.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731232/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731232/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731232/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-21","Lebanon: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent diplomatic and other support the Government has given to the Lebanese Government to assist it with the influx of refugees into that country.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731233","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>​We have not made representations to the Government of Lebanon on this issue. Whilst we recognise there are concerns, this is ultimately a matter for the Lebanese government.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-06-29T12:42:49.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731233/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731233/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731233/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-21","Lebanon: Historic Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the Government of Lebanon on the planned demolition of historical buildings of international significance in Beirut.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731234","Department for Transport","false","2017-06-28","<p>As with all transport scheme proposals a thorough analysis is being carried out by my department to ensure it is a robust scheme. This includes examining whether the National Infrastructure Commission’s detailed recommendations on the scheme have been taken into account. The next steps and timescales, including when the next stage of public consultation will take place, will therefore be decided as part of this analysis.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard","205 ; 206","2017-06-28T13:41:26.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731234/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731234/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731234/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-06-21","Crossrail 2 Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he plans to respond to Transport for London's Strategic Outline Business Case for Crossrail 2.","false","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","204"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731235","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>We have not had any discussions with the Israeli authorities on this issue.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-06-29T12:44:10.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731235/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731235/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731235/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-21","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions his Department has had with the Israeli Government on encouraging more Palestinians to seek Israeli citizenship.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","375"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731236","HM Treasury","false","2017-06-28","<p>The government fully supports the principles of better debt management and lower levels of problem debt. This government has a manifesto commitment to introduce a statutory breathing space that would give heavily indebted consumers a period of respite from enforcement action, and further interest and charges for a period of up to six weeks. Where appropriate, they will be offered a statutory repayment plan to help them pay back their debts in a sustainable way. We will outline further information in due course.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-06-28T15:24:54.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731236/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731236/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731236/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-06-21","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when the Government plans to bring forward legislative proposals on the breathing space mechanism for families in debt.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","121"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731237","Department for Education","false","2017-06-30","<p>Parents play a vitally important role in their child’s early development and learning.</p><p>The What to Expect When Guide, funded by the Department for Education (DfE), sets out the development milestones at each age in key areas to help parents support their children. <a href="http://www.foundationyears.org.uk/2015/03/what-to-expect-when-a-parents-guide/" target="_blank">http://www.foundationyears.org.uk/2015/03/what-to-expect-when-a-parents-guide/</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The Early Years Foundation Stage Framework (EYFS) statutory framework requires that early years settings must engage parents and carers in guiding their child’s development at home. In 2017, the Department awarded grants totalling almost £1.7m to voluntary and community sector organisations. These grants support work with disadvantaged communities to improve the take-up of free early education places for 2-year olds, and work with parents to create a positive home learning environment.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England is leading a programme of work to ensure that at least 30,000 more women each year are able to access evidence-based specialist mental health care during the perinatal period by 2020/21. £60m has been committed to improve the provision of specialist perinatal community services across England between 2016/17 and 2018/19, promoting equality of access across the communities they serve.</p><p>Increasing capability across the specialist perinatal mental health workforce is also a key objective. Targeted funding of £1.2m in 2017/18 will enable the training of mental health, maternity and primary care staff, increasing awareness and skills related to perinatal mental health.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-06-30T13:11:48.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731237/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731237/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731237/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-06-21","Children: Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps she is taking to improve the (a) quality of attachment between parents and children aged under five, (b) home learning environments for children aged under five and (c) mental health of new and expectant mothers in low-income households.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","122"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731238","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Government remains absolutely committed to LGBT equality and the Prime Minister has been very clear that any arrangement with the DUP will not affect LGBT rights in the UK.</p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2017-06-29T15:19:16.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731238/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731238/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731238/answer","Ashford","Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731238/answer/previousversion/110","Biography information for Damian Green","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-21","LGBT People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the protection and promotion of LGBT rights was discussed at recent meetings with the leadership of the Democratic Unionist Party.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731239","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Government remains absolutely committed to the protection and promotion of women’s rights. The Prime Minister has been very clear that any arrangement with the DUP will not affect women’s rights in the UK.</p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2017-06-29T15:21:56.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731239/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731239/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731239/answer","Ashford","Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731239/answer/previousversion/113","Biography information for Damian Green","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-21","Human Rights: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the protection and promotion of women's rights was discussed at recent meetings with the leadership of the Democratic Unionist Party.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731240","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-06-26","<p>The Government is committed to supporting working parents with premature babies. We are working with the Advisory, Conciliation &amp; Arbitration Service (Acas) to produce best practice guidance for employers on how best to support working parents with babies born prematurely. We expect guidance to be published in the autumn.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-06-26T14:36:36.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731240/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731240/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731240/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-06-21","Working Mothers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the announcement made by his Department on 27 March 2017 on new guidance to support working mothers of premature babies, what progress has been made on drawing up of such guidance; and whether it is still the Government's policy to publish guidance for employers.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","165"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731241","Department of Health","false","2017-06-26","<p>The Department is working in conjunction with NHS England to test a prototype new dental contract with an increased focus on prevention. The remuneration system is designed to better support dentists to prevent as well as treat disease and maintain the numbers of patients they care for.</p><p> </p><p>The trial of the new clinical and remuneration approach began in April 2016 with prototype practices across England testing the new way of working. The scheme is being evaluated and the substantive report on the scheme to date is expected to be available later this year. Decisions on next steps and any wider roll out will be based on the learning from the prototype scheme.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-06-26T14:03:35.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731241/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731241/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731241/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-06-21","Dental Services: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what progress has been made on the rollout of a new contract to dental care providers.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","167"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731242","Prime Minister","false","2017-06-30","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the statement issued on 19 June following my meeting with Taoiseach Leo Varadkar and which is available on the gov.uk website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/pm-press-conference-with-taoiseach-leo-varadkar-19-june-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/pm-press-conference-with-taoiseach-leo-varadkar-19-june-2017</a></p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2017-06-30T12:00:16.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731242/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731242/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731242/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2017-06-21","Borders: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, whether she plans to discuss the land border between Northern Ireland and the Republic of Ireland when she meets Taoiseach Leo Varadkar.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","143"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731243","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-27","<p>The government is working on a new Anti-Corruption Strategy which will be published in due course.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-06-27T14:59:57.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731243/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731243/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731243/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-21","Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when the Government plans to publish its Anti-Corruption Strategy.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","144"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731244","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-28","<p>Progress on the anti-corruption commitments made at the 2016 Summit is continuously monitored.</p><p> </p><p>The UK has made good progress. Since last May, we have for example:</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>● Established a public central register of beneficial ownership information;</p><p>● Introduced Unexplained Wealth Orders and other important anti-corruption measures through the Criminal Finances Act;</p><p>● Undergone the first IMF Fiscal Transparency Evaluation for a G7 country; and</p><p>● Launched the ‘Contracting 5’ (C5) initiative at the Open Government Partnership Global Summit 2016 with Colombia, France, Mexico, and Ukraine.</p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-06-28T15:43:47.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731244/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731244/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731244/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-21","Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when he plans to review progress on the commitments made at the 2016 International Anti-Corruption Summit; and what the timetable is for further reviews of that progress.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","145"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731245","Department for Education","false","2017-06-30","<p>The Government is committed to ensuring that all children – regardless of background – get the best possible start in life. Children’s centres are part of this.</p><p>We will set out our plans in due course.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-06-30T13:04:31.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731245/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731245/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731245/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-06-21","Children's Centres","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when she plans to publish the consultation on the future of Sure Start children's centres.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","147"
