"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731247","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-28","<p>A decision on the anti-corruption champion appointment will be made in due course.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-06-28T15:45:08.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731247/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731247/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731247/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-21","Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when he plans to appoint an anti-corruption champion.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","150"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731248","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Prime Minister and this Government have been consistently clear on both these issues, and they are explored in detail in pages 35 to 49 of the Government's White Paper <em>The United Kingdom's exit from and new partnership with the European Union</em>.</p><p>We will not seek membership of the Single Market after we leave the EU, but will pursue instead a bold and ambitious Free Trade Agreement as part of a new, deep and special partnership. In doing so, we will take back control of our laws and bring an end to the direct jurisdiction of the Court of Justice of the EU in the UK.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-06-29T10:12:45.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731248/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731248/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731248/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-06-21","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether it remains the position of the Government that the UK should withdraw from both the customs union and the single market.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731249","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-06-28","<p>The Government received a broad range of responses to the call for evidence on economic crime. Many submissions raised complex issues and the MOJ is currently analysing these before reporting in due course.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-06-28T15:23:32.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731249/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731249/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731249/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-06-21","Fraud: Criminal Liability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when he plans to publish the results of the call for evidence on corporate criminal liability for economic crime.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731250","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-06-27","<p>The Department robustly monitors the performance of contracted suppliers and assessments are independently audited to ensure that the advice provided to the Department’s decision makers is of suitable quality, fully explained and justified. Assessment reports deemed unacceptable are returned to the provider for reworking. We continue to work extensively with PIP assessment providers to make improvements to guidance, training and audit procedures in order to ensure a quality service is maintained.</p><p> </p><p>The Contractual target is 97% acceptable reports.</p><p> </p><p>Detailed guidance on how reports are audited and the criteria to be used are set out in section 4.5 of the Personal Independence Payment Assessment Guide, which can be found here <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/547146/pip-assessment-guide.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/547146/pip-assessment-guide.pdf</a>.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-06-27T15:11:06.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731250/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731250/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731250/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-06-21","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what indicators his Department plans to use to measure the quality of assessment reports produced by personal independence payment assessment suppliers.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","123"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731251","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-06-30","<p>In (a) Wales Community Rehabilitation Company 4.68 Full Time Equivalent Employment and Training staff are employed. In (b)Bristol, Gloucestershire, Somerset and Wiltshire Community Rehabilitation company,12.28 Full Time Equivalent Employment and Training staff are employed</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-06-30T13:32:40.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731251/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731251/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731251/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-06-21","Community Rehabilitation Companies: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many employment and training staff were employed by the Community Rehabilitation Company in (a) Wales and (b) Bristol, Gloucestershire, Somerset and Wiltshire Community Rehabilitation Company at the latest date for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","125"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731252","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-28","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-06-28T15:56:28.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731252/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731252/answer","PQ 152 v.02 (2).pdf","UKSA Response to PQ152","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731252/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-21","Zero Hours Contracts: Linlithgow and East Falkirk","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people in Linlithgow and East Falkirk constituency are employed on zero-hours contracts; how many of those people are (a) aged between 16 and 24-years old and (b) women.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","152"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731253","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-06-30","<p>It has not been possible to answer this question in the time allowed. I will write to the honourable member in due course.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-06-30T11:58:41.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731253/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731253/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731253/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-06-21","Criminal Injuries Compensation: Offences against Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of the Criminal Injuries Compensation Scheme's policy on consent to sexual assault on victims who are under 16 years of age and do not qualify for compensation.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","126"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731254","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-14","<p>Local authorities are Category 1 responders under the Civil Contingencies Act 2004. Category 1 responders are subject to the full set of civil protection duties. They are required to assess the risk of emergencies occurring and use this to inform contingency planning. They are also required to put in place emergency plans. The Government has also issued non-statutory guidance in the 2014 Evacuation and Shelter Guidance for local emergency planners.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-14T10:52:00.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731254/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731254/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731254/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-06-21","Temporary Accommodation: Emergencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of placing a requirement on councils to have emergency plans in place for rehousing and compensating residents in the event of a disaster.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","127"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731255","Department for Education","false","2017-06-27","<p>There was no education bill in the Queen’s Speech, and therefore the ban on opening new grammar schools will remain in place.</p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2017-06-27T08:29:55.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731255/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731255/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731255/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-06-21","Grammar Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether it remains the Government's policy to allow the opening of new grammar schools.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","128"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731256","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-06-30","<p>This information is not collected centrally and can only be obtained at disproportionate cost. There is no contractual requirement for the CRC to collect this information.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-06-30T13:34:09.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731256/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731256/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731256/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-06-21","Wales Community Rehabilitation Company","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many offenders were seen each week by employment and training staff in the Community Rehabilitation Company in Wales in the last period for which figures are available; and what payment that company received for each person seen.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","129"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731257","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-06-28","<p>In 2015, 23,057 restraining orders were issued in total by all courts in England and Wales.</p><p>Information on the specific restrictions within each restraining order is held on individual court files and could therefore only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-06-28T15:26:12.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731257/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731257/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731257/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-06-21","Restraining Orders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many restraining orders were issued by courts in England and Wales during 2015; and of those orders how many prohibited online contact via any social media platform.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","130"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731258","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-06-28","<p><strong>The Department is recruiting the brightest and the best from across the civil service, the wider public sector and the private sector. The Department for Exiting the European Union now has over 450 staff, and is growing fast. </strong></p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-06-28T12:33:53.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731258/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731258/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731258/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-06-21","Department for Exiting the European Union: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many staff are employed by his Department.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","134"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731259","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Government was clear in its White Paper that we aim to have as seamless and frictionless a border as possible between Northern Ireland and Ireland. There is a very strong commitment from the UK and Irish Governments to find a practical solution that recognises the unique circumstances on the land border between Northern Ireland and Ireland. We welcome the European Council’s commitment to develop flexible and imaginative solutions, and the establishment of a dialogue between the UK and EU Commission to discuss this issue.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-06-29T10:18:57.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731259/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731259/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731259/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-06-21","Borders: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what assessment he has made of the effect of withdrawing from the Customs Union on the land border between Northern Ireland and the Republic of Ireland.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","131"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731260","Women and Equalities","false","2017-08-31","<p>My Rt hon. Friend, the Secretary of State, has ongoing discussions with my Rt hon. Friend, the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, on a number of issues that affect government, and my Rt hon. Friend, the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, has a continued dialogue with members of the Northern Ireland Executive. My Rt hon. Friend, the Secretary of State, in her recent debate on equality and women’s rights in the House, gave reassurances that we will continue to strengthen our progressive record on equality and human rights as we work with others to govern in the national interest.</p><p> </p><p>Work continues in preparation for the UK’s 8<sup>th</sup> Periodic Report to the Committee on the UN Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Discrimination Against Women (CEDAW) – a core human rights treaty which focuses on rights equality between women and men in all aspects of life.</p><p> </p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-08-31T15:51:38.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731260/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731260/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731260/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-06-21","Females: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what recent discussions she has had with (a) the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland and (b) Members of Northern Ireland Executive on the protection and promotion of women's rights in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","135"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731261","Women and Equalities","false","2017-07-12","<p>The Government is committed to progress LGBT equality globally and is working hard with like minded countries to share best practice, notably through the Equal Rights Coalition, of which the United Kingdom is a founding member. The United Kingdom has made progress in promoting LGBT equality: we have one of the world’s strongest legislative frameworks to prevent and tackle discrimination. We are, however, not complacent and we are working hard to improve our legislation and policies. As we work with others to govern in the national interest, we will continue to promote and champion the equal rights we believe in.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-07-12T16:32:56.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731261/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731261/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731261/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-06-21","LGBT People: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what recent discussions she has had with (a) the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland and (b) Members of Northern Ireland Executive on the protection and promotion of LGBT rights in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731262","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-06-30","<p>There are already safeguards in place to protect social tenants who lose their homes in a disaster. We would expect local authorities or housing associations to take steps to rehouse any existing social tenants whose existing home is destroyed or made uninhabitable in a fire or other disaster.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-06-30T15:49:21.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731262/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731262/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731262/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-06-21","Temporary Accommodation: Emergencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans his Department has to require local councils to rehouse social tenants displaced due to disaster within their local area.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731263","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Government has published the terms of the supply and confidence agreement between the Conservative Party and DUP. The agreement ensures DUP support on votes on the Queen’s Speech, the Budget, and on legislation relating to our exit from the European Union and national security. All other matters will be agreed on a case by case basis.</p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2017-06-29T15:25:47.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731263/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731263/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731263/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-21","Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether tackling climate change was discussed at recent meetings with the DUP leadership.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","137"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731264","Women and Equalities","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Government believes that both Christians and people of other religious beliefs should be able to wear or carry religious symbols in public so long as they act within the boundaries of the law while doing so.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-06-29T16:37:54.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731264/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731264/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731264/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-06-21","Religious Freedom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what the Government's policy is on protecting the right of (a) Christians and (b) people of other religious beliefs to wear or carry religious symbols in public.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","168"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731265","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-17","<p>Although registration initiatives in Northern Ireland are an operational matter for the Chief Electoral Officer, the Government fully supports initiatives to encourage registration among young people. The Electoral Office for Northern Ireland continues to implement its Schools Programme which registers students in school sixth forms and also continues to engage with further education colleges across Northern Ireland in relation to holding registration clinics.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Electoral Office for Northern Ireland also routinely receives information from further education colleges across Northern Ireland and this information is used to write to all college students not already registered to encourage registration.</p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-07-17T15:34:11.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731265/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731265/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731265/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-21","Electoral Register: Students","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps the Government is taking to encourage sixth form and technical colleges to contact electoral offices to provide registration days and ID provision before any future elections.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","169"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731266","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Government remains absolutely committed to LGBT equality and the Prime Minister has been very clear that any arrangement with the DUP will not affect LGBT rights in the UK. The priorities for the deal between the Conservative party and the DUP have been set out in the agreement.</p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2017-06-29T15:10:49.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731266/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731266/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731266/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-21","LGBT People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what recent discussions he has had with Ruth Davidson MSP on (a) promoting LGBT rights across all countries within the UK and (b) the priorities for the Government's deal with the DUP.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","141"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731267","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-28","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-06-28T15:58:24.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731267/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731267/answer","PQ182 v.02 (1).pdf","UKSA Response to PQ182","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731267/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-21","Unemployment: Linlithgow and East Falkirk","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many workless households there are in Linlithgow and East Falkirk constituency.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731268","Cabinet Office","false","2017-06-28","<p>The total cost to the public purse of administering the 2017 UK parliamentary general election comprises two main elements: the expenditure incurred by Returning Officers in running the poll; and the cost of delivering election mailings produced by candidates. Returning Officers will have six months from the day of the poll to submit their expense claims, and so the final cost will not be known until these have been received, scrutinised and settled. The actual cost of delivering candidates’ mailings will also not be known until all invoices from the universal service provider (Royal Mail) have been received and settled.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The total amount accrued to the public purse as a result of candidates losing their deposits at the 2017 UK general election is not yet available.</p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-06-28T15:39:04.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731268/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731268/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731268/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-06-21","General Election 2017","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of (a) the cost to the public purse of administering the 2017 General Election and (b) the amount that accrued to the public purse as a result of candidates losing their deposits at that election.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","183"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731269","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-06-27","<p>We want to see disabled people and people with health conditions, including those living with arthritis and musculoskeletal conditions, to fulfil their full potential in work and go as far as their talents and drive can take them.</p><p> </p><p>We are reforming current Government schemes that support disabled people and those with health conditions to return to and stay in work, for example through Access to Work. Access to Work is a grant scheme for individuals to cover the additional costs of working that arise as a result of a disability or health condition. We are also encouraging all employers to sign-up to the Disability Confident scheme which is designed to help employers access the talents of disabled people and retain them in the workplace.</p><p> </p><p>The Work, Health and Disability Green paper set out plans to develop a 10-year strategy that focuses on transforming employment prospects of disabled people and people with long term health conditions – both by getting people into work as well as retaining those already in employment. The government is committed to ensuring disabled people have better employment outcomes.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-06-27T14:43:38.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731269/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731269/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731269/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-06-21","Employment: Musculoskeletal Disorders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department is taking to support people with arthritis and musculoskeletal conditions to return to and to stay in work.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","184"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731270","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-06-30","<p>The Secretary of State for Culture has regular discussions with the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union (EU) on a range of issues affecting the creative and cultural industries in the context of leaving the EU.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-06-30T12:00:23.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731270/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731270/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731270/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-06-21","Culture: EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions she has had with the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union on the UK's participation in Creative Europe.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731271","Home Office","false","2017-06-26","<p>A temporary hold on decision-making in respect of some partner visa applications was introduced on 22 February 2017 so that the implications of the Supreme Court judgment handed down that day in MM (Lebanon) &amp; Others could be considered.</p><p>UKVI communicated this to potential priority visa service customers on 27 February 2017 and will consider any refund requests from customers who paid the priority service fee for a settlement visa before 27 February 2017 and whose application was put on hold by the Home Office. These requests should be made via the usual enquiry helpline: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/uk-visas-and-immigration/about/complaints-procedure#how-to-complain" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/uk-visas-and-immigration/about/complaints-procedure#how-to-complain</a></p><p>Both UK Visas and Immigration and their commercial partners make clear in communications to customers that the priority visa service fee will not be refunded if the visa is refused or takes longer than the publicised processing times, other than in exceptional circumstances.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-06-26T16:45:26.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731271/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731271/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731271/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-21","Visas: Married People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking to refund fast track payments made by applicants for partner visas where the processing of those applications has been suspended as a result of the legal challenge to the Government's minimum income requirement.","false","Biography information for Peter Grant","Glenrothes","Peter Grant","216"
