"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731292","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-06-30","<p>The Government is working with food businesses through a voluntary approach to reduce food waste, including through redistribution when surplus food cannot be avoided. Business signatories to the Courtauld 2025 Commitment are aiming to double the amount of food surplus they send for redistribution between 2015 and 2020. We do not have plans to legislate.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-06-30T12:03:02.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731292/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731292/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/731292/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-06-21","Food: Charitable Donations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to ensure that more surplus food is redistributed by retailers to charities supporting those experiencing hunger and food poverty.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","63"
